race.comment: The Matthew Dunn-trained RUPESTRIS (2) returns from a six-month spell and has been gelded. Raced once in the maiden prep and wasn't beaten far over 1110m at Doomben. Trialled well at the Gold Coast recently and looks set for a big return. EGYPTIAN LASS (5) was easily accounted for in a small field over this course and distance seven days ago. Well drawn so although her form isn't great in a weak maiden she can figure prominently. STRATTON (7) didn't finish his race off as hoped in a 1300m maiden at Ballina last time out. Placed here at this trip last prep and cannot be ruled out. SURAT DISTRICT (8) resumes after a 14-week break. Did little last prep which was punctuated by a stable change. Might have more to offer this time in work. PRESTIGE GUNDY (3) can improve after tackling a strong maiden on debut last start. ZALENKA (9) and DAZZLING PEACE (1) are first starters worth monitoring for market support.
